{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874830001,"sessionID":"ses_2859d2437ffeNuXqfOaUiqxVoL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a62fb16001CxYM4RQbw0EbJK","messageID":"msg_d7a62ec6a0015Ubt5DHURkh8gy","sessionID":"ses_2859d2437ffeNuXqfOaUiqxVoL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_eabe55c39d454dafbb49416f","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement `CodeInterpreterClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK to provide a high-level interface for:\n- Creating and managing Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane)\n- Executing code and managing files via the Router (data plane)\n\nThis client abstracts the complexity of control plane and data plane communication, providing a simple context-manager-based API for developers.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **Core Client Implementation**\n   - `CodeInterpreterClient` class in `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n   - Context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n   - Session lifecycle management (create, use, delete)\n\n2. **Control Plane Integration**\n   - `ControlPlaneClient` for session creation/deletion via Workload Manager\n   - URL and authentication token resolution from arguments or environment\n\n3. **Data Plane Integration**\n   - `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` for executing commands and file operations\n   - Router-relative URL construction\n   - Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n\n4. **Public API Methods**\n   - `execute_command(command, timeout)` - Execute shell commands\n   - `run_code(language, code, timeout)` - Execute Python/other language code\n   - `write_file(content, remote_path)` - Write file content (base64)\n   - `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` - Upload file (multipart)\n   - `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` - Download file\n   - `list_files(path)` - List directory contents\n   - `stop()` - Cleanup and delete session\n\n5. **Supporting Components**\n   - Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`)\n   - HTTP session creation with connection pooling\n   - Token reading from service account file\n   - Logging utilities\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Direct exports of lower-level clients (`ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`) from root package\n- Custom configuration classes (uses distributed configuration pattern)\n- Non-Python language execution special handling beyond basic command routing\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files to Create/Modify\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Create | Export `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | Create | Main `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | Create | `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation |\n| `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Create | Re-export client classes |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Create | Control plane HTTP client |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Create | Data plane HTTP client for Code Interpreter |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Create | Data plane HTTP client for Agent Runtime |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Create | `create_session` helper |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Create | `read_token_from_file` helper |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Create | `get_logger` helper |\n| `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Create | Module marker |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Create | Exception hierarchy |\n| `pyproject.toml` | Create | Package configuration with dependencies |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `requests` - HTTP client library\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0` - JWT handling (future extensibility)\n- `cryptography` - Cryptographic primitives (future extensibility)\n- Python >= 3.10\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\nThis is a new feature with no existing users. No backward compatibility concerns.\n\n### Testing Impact\n\nTest files should cover:\n- Context manager lifecycle and cleanup\n- Session creation/deletion flows\n- Command execution with non-zero exit codes\n- File upload/download operations\n- Error handling and exception raising\n- Environment variable fallback behavior\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Single Configuration Class\n\n**Approach:** Create a dedicated `Configuration` dataclass to hold all settings (URLs, tokens, timeouts).\n\n**Pros:**\n- Centralized configuration management\n- Easier to validate configuration at initialization\n- Cleaner API surface\n\n**Cons:**\n- Adds abstraction layer not needed for current use cases\n- More boilerplate for simple SDK\n- Less flexible for per-client customization\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. The distributed configuration pattern (each client resolves its own settings from args/env) is simpler and more aligned with the existing design spec.\n\n### Alternative 2: Async/Await HTTP Client\n\n**Approach:** Use `aiohttp` or `httpx` for async HTTP operations.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Better performance for concurrent operations\n- Modern async API patterns\n\n**Cons:**\n- Increased complexity for users not using async code\n- Additional dependency burden\n- Not required for typical single-session use cases\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. The synchronous `requests` library is sufficient for the target use cases and provides a simpler API for users.\n\n### Alternative 3: Automatic Session Reuse\n\n**Approach:** Automatically detect and reuse existing sessions based on `name` and `namespace`.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Could reduce session creation overhead\n- More convenient for repeated runs\n\n**Cons:**\n- Adds complexity to session management\n- Potential for unintended session reuse\n- TTL-based cleanup becomes ambiguous\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Explicit `session_id` parameter provides clearer control; users can manually reuse sessions by passing `session_id`.\n\n## Implementation Approach\n\n1. **Create package structure** - Set up all directories and module files\n2. **Implement utilities** - HTTP session creation, token reading, logging\n3. **Implement exception hierarchy** - Base and specific exception classes\n4. **Implement control plane client** - Session CRUD operations with Workload Manager\n5. **Implement data plane clients** - Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime HTTP clients\n6. **Implement high-level clients** - `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` with context manager support\n7. **Configure package** - Set up `pyproject.toml` with dependencies and build configuration\n\n## Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Router API contract changes | Low | High | Versioned API paths (`/v1/...`), clear error messages |\n| Service account token path varies | Low | Medium | Fallback to empty token, clear error on auth failure |\n| Timeout edge cases | Medium | Low | Buffer read timeout (+2.0s) to avoid premature `ReadTimeout` |\n| Session cleanup failures | Medium | Low | Log warnings, ensure HTTP session closure even on errors |\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `CodeInterpreterClient` can create and delete sessions via control plane\n2. ✅ Code execution works with proper timeout handling\n3. ✅ File operations (upload/download/write/list) function correctly\n4. ✅ Context manager properly cleans up resources on exit\n5. ✅ All exception scenarios raise appropriate error types\n6. ✅ Environment variable fallbacks work as specified\n7. ✅ Package installs and imports correctly with documented dependencies\n"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775874829989,"end":1775874829997}}}}
