{"type":"text","timestamp":1775874839439,"sessionID":"ses_2859d2437ffeNuXqfOaUiqxVoL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a63909c001mESxr0ekOcQm1g","messageID":"msg_d7a638117001Eaz3O200m5BY9V","sessionID":"ses_2859d2437ffeNuXqfOaUiqxVoL","type":"text","text":"I see there's already a proposal.md file for AR-025. I'll create the new proposal for AR-027 (SDK CodeInterpreterClient) as requested in the `.sdd_prompt.md` file.","time":{"start":1775874839437,"end":1775874839437}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775874973006,"sessionID":"ses_2859d2437ffeNuXqfOaUiqxVoL","part":{"id":"prt_d7a639390001ZgL4dht7AqArIg","messageID":"msg_d7a638117001Eaz3O200m5BY9V","sessionID":"ses_2859d2437ffeNuXqfOaUiqxVoL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_867664c63cde44139ac999f0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `CodeInterpreterClient` for the AgentCube Python SDK (`sdk-python`). The goal is to:\n\n1. **Provide high-level session management** - Abstract control plane session creation and data plane communication\n2. **Enable code execution** - Execute Python code and shell commands in remote Code Interpreter sessions\n3. **Support file operations** - Upload, download, write, and list files in the interpreter environment\n4. **Ensure clean lifecycle** - Context manager protocol for automatic session cleanup and resource deallocation\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**\n  - `CodeInterpreterClient` class with context manager support\n  - `ControlPlaneClient` for session CRUD via Workload Manager\n  - `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` for data plane operations via Router\n  - Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`)\n  - HTTP session management with connection pooling\n  - Environment variable and file-based authentication token resolution\n  - `AgentRuntimeClient` for Agent Runtime invocations\n\n- **Out of scope:**\n  - Direct user-facing CLI commands (separate AR)\n  - Kubernetes CRD management (handled by CLI toolkit)\n  - Async/await HTTP client patterns\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### Existing Implementation\n\nPer the design specification (`python-sdk/design.md`), the following components are defined:\n\n1. **Package Layout:**\n   - `agentcube/__init__.py` - Public exports (`CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient`)\n   - `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` - `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation\n   - `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` - `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation\n   - `agentcube/clients/` - Low-level HTTP clients\n   - `agentcube/utils/` - HTTP session, logging, token utilities\n   - `agentcube/exceptions.py` - Exception hierarchy\n\n2. **Configuration Pattern:**\n   - No single `Configuration` class\n   - Distributed configuration: each client resolves its own settings from arguments or environment variables\n\n3. **HTTP Contracts:**\n   - Control plane: `POST/DELETE {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n   - Data plane: `POST/GET {base_url}/api/*` (Router-relative paths)\n\n### Issues Identified\n\n1. **Session header naming** - Must use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` for consistency\n2. **Timeout handling** - Read timeout needs +2.0s buffer to avoid premature `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124\n3. **Exception usage** - `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core client modules\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### 1. Exception Hierarchy\n\nImplement in `agentcube/exceptions.py`:\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n    pass\n\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when a remote command fails with non-zero exit code.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: str = None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### 2. ControlPlaneClient\n\nImplement in `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`:\n\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ):\n        self.base_url = workload_manager_url or os.getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")\n        if not self.base_url:\n            raise ValueError(\"workload_manager_url must be provided or set via WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")\n        \n        self.timeout = timeout\n        self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n        \n        # Resolve auth token\n        token = auth_token\n        if not token:\n            sa_token_path = \"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\"\n            token = read_token_from_file(sa_token_path)\n        \n        self.session = create_session(pool_connections=pool_connections, pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize)\n        self.session.headers[\"Content-Type\"] = \"application/json\"\n        if token:\n            self.session.headers[\"Authorization\"] = f\"Bearer {token}\"\n    \n    def create_session(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Create a Code Interpreter session via Workload Manager.\"\"\"\n        url = f\"{self.base_url}/v1/code-interpreter\"\n        payload = {\n            \"name\": name,\n            \"namespace\": namespace,\n            \"ttl\": ttl,\n            \"metadata\": metadata or {},\n        }\n        response = self.session.post(\n            url,\n            json=payload,\n            timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        data = response.json()\n        session_id = data.get(\"sessionId\")\n        if not session_id:\n            raise ValueError(\"create_session response missing 'sessionId'\")\n        return session_id\n    \n    def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Delete a Code Interpreter session. Returns True on success or 404.\"\"\"\n        url = f\"{self.base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}\"\n        try:\n            response = self.session.delete(\n                url,\n                timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n            )\n            if response.status_code == 404:\n                return True\n            response.raise_for_status()\n            return True\n        except requests.RequestException as e:\n            logger.warning(f\"delete_session failed: {e}\")\n            return False\n    \n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close the HTTP session.\"\"\"\n        self.session.close()\n```\n\n### 3. CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\nImplement in `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`:\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n        cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n        base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ):\n        self.session_id = session_id\n        self.timeout = timeout\n        self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n        \n        # Resolve base_url\n        if base_url:\n            self.base_url = base_url\n        else:\n            if not router_url or not namespace or not cr_name:\n                raise ValueError(\"base_url or (router_url, namespace, cr_name) must be provided\")\n            base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n            self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n        \n        self.session = create_session(pool_connections=pool_connections, pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize)\n        self.session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"] = session_id\n    \n    def _request(\n        self,\n        method: str,\n        endpoint: str,\n        body: Optional[bytes] = None,\n        **kwargs,\n    ) -> requests.Response:\n        \"\"\"Internal request helper.\"\"\"\n        url = urljoin(self.base_url, endpoint)\n        headers = kwargs.pop(\"headers\", {})\n        if body:\n            headers[\"Content-Type\"] = \"application/json\"\n        \n        timeout = kwargs.pop(\"timeout\", (self.connect_timeout, self.timeout))\n        \n        response = self.session.request(\n            method,\n            url,\n            data=body,\n            headers=headers,\n            timeout=timeout,\n            **kwargs,\n        )\n        return response\n    \n    def execute_command(\n        self,\n        command: Union[str, List[str]],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Execute a shell command in the Code Interpreter.\"\"\"\n        timeout_value = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n        \n        if isinstance(command, str):\n            command = [command]\n        \n        # Build timeout string for PicoD\n        timeout_str = f\"{int(timeout_value)}s\"\n        \n        # Calculate read timeout with buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\n        read_timeout = timeout_value + 2.0 if isinstance(timeout_value, (int, float)) else timeout_value\n        \n        body = json.dumps({\n            \"command\": command,\n            \"timeout\": timeout_str,\n        }).encode(\"utf-8\")\n        \n        response = self._request(\n            \"POST\",\n            \"api/execute\",\n            body=body,\n            timeout=(self.connect_timeout, read_timeout),\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        data = response.json()\n        \n        exit_code = data.get(\"exit_code\", 0)\n        if exit_code != 0:\n            stderr = data.get(\"stderr\", \"Unknown error\")\n            raise CommandExecutionError(\n                exit_code=exit_code,\n                stderr=stderr,\n                command=command,\n            )\n        \n        return data.get(\"stdout\", \"\")\n    \n    def run_code(\n        self,\n        language: str,\n        code: str,\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Execute code in the specified language.\"\"\"\n        if language.lower() in (\"python\", \"py\", \"python3\"):\n            # Write code to timestamped file\n            timestamp = datetime.utcnow().strftime(\"%Y%m%d%H%M%S%f\")\n            remote_path = f\"/tmp/code_{timestamp}.py\"\n            self.write_file(code, remote_path)\n            \n            # Execute via python3\n            return self.execute_command([\"python3\", remote_path], timeout=timeout)\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {language}\")\n    \n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Write file content via base64 encoding.\"\"\"\n        import base64\n        encoded = base64.b64encode(content.encode(\"utf-8\")).decode(\"utf-8\")\n        \n        body = json.dumps({\n            \"path\": remote_path,\n            \"content\": encoded,\n            \"mode\": \"0644\",\n        }).encode(\"utf-8\")\n        \n        response = self._request(\n            \"POST\",\n            \"api/files\",\n            body=body,\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n    \n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Upload a file via multipart form.\"\"\"\n        with open(local_path, \"rb\") as f:\n            files = {\"file\": f}\n            data = {\n                \"path\": remote_path,\n                \"mode\": \"0644\",\n            }\n            \n            # Multipart upload - don't set Content-Type header\n            url = urljoin(self.base_url, \"api/files\")\n            response = self.session.post(\n                url,\n                files=files,\n                data=data,\n                headers={\"x-agentcube-session-id\": self.session_id},\n                timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n            )\n            response.raise_for_status()\n    \n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Download a file from the Code Interpreter.\"\"\"\n        clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")\n        response = self._request(\n            \"GET\",\n            f\"api/files/{clean_path}\",\n            stream=True,\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        \n        with open(local_path, \"wb\") as f:\n            for chunk in response.iter_content(chunk_size=8192):\n                f.write(chunk)\n    \n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n        \"\"\"List files in a directory.\"\"\"\n        response = self._request(\n            \"GET\",\n            \"api/files\",\n            params={\"path\": path},\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response.json()\n    \n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close the HTTP session.\"\"\"\n        self.session.close()\n```\n\n### 4. CodeInterpreterClient (High-Level Client)\n\nImplement in `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`:\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    \"\"\"High-level client for Code Interpreter operations.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n    ):\n        self.name = name\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.ttl = ttl\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.session_id = session_id\n        \n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n        \n        # Initialize control plane client\n        self.cp_client = ControlPlaneClient(\n            workload_manager_url=workload_manager_url,\n            auth_token=auth_token,\n        )\n        \n        # Resolve router URL\n        self.router_url = router_url or os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n        if not self.router_url:\n            raise ValueError(\"router_url must be provided or set via ROUTER_URL\")\n        \n        # Create session if session_id not provided\n        if not self.session_id:\n            self.session_id = self.cp_client.create_session(\n                name=name,\n                namespace=namespace,\n                ttl=ttl,\n            )\n            self.logger.info(f\"Created session: {self.session_id}\")\n        \n        # Initialize data plane client\n        try:\n            self._init_data_plane()\n        except Exception as e:\n            # Cleanup on failure\n            self.logger.warning(f\"Data plane init failed: {e}, cleaning up session\")\n            self.cp_client.delete_session(self.session_id)\n            self.session_id = None\n            raise\n    \n    def _init_data_plane(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize the data plane client.\"\"\"\n        self.dp_client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n            session_id=self.session_id,\n            router_url=self.router_url,\n            namespace=self.namespace,\n            cr_name=self.name,\n        )\n    \n    def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\":\n        return self\n    \n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n        self.stop()\n    \n    def stop(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Stop the Code Interpreter session.\"\"\"\n        self.logger.info(\"Stopping CodeInterpreterClient\")\n        \n        # Close data plane\n        if hasattr(self, \"dp_client\") and self.dp_client:\n            self.dp_client.close()\n        \n        # Delete control plane session\n        if self.session_id:\n            self.cp_client.delete_session(self.session_id)\n            self.logger.info(f\"Deleted session: {self.session_id}\")\n            self.session_id = None\n        \n        # Close control plane\n        self.cp_client.close()\n    \n    def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Execute a shell command.\"\"\"\n        return self.dp_client.execute_command(command, timeout=timeout)\n    \n    def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Execute code in the specified language.\"\"\"\n        return self.dp_client.run_code(language, code, timeout=timeout)\n    \n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Write file content.\"\"\"\n        self.dp_client.write_file(content, remote_path)\n    \n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Upload a file.\"\"\"\n        self.dp_client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)\n    \n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Download a file.\"\"\"\n        self.dp_client.download_file(remote_path, local_path)\n    \n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n        \"\"\"List files in a directory.\"\"\"\n        return self.dp_client.list_files(path)\n```\n\n### 5. AgentRuntimeClient\n\nImplement in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`:\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    \"\"\"High-level client for Agent Runtime invocations.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ):\n        self.agent_name = agent_name\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.timeout = timeout\n        self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n        self.session_id = session_id\n        \n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n        \n        # Resolve router URL\n        self.router_url = router_url or os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n        if not self.router_url:\n            raise ValueError(\"router_url must be provided or set via ROUTER_URL\")\n        \n        # Bootstrap session_id if not provided\n        if not self.session_id:\n            self._bootstrap_session_id()\n        \n        # Initialize data plane client\n        self.dp_client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=self.router_url,\n            namespace=self.namespace,\n            agent_name=self.agent_name,\n            timeout=self.timeout,\n            connect_timeout=self.connect_timeout,\n        )\n    \n    def _bootstrap_session_id(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Bootstrap session_id from Agent Runtime invocation endpoint.\"\"\"\n        base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{self.namespace}/agent-runtimes/{self.agent_name}/invocations/\"\n        base_url = urljoin(self.router_url, base_path)\n        \n        session = create_session()\n        try:\n            response = session.get(\n                base_url,\n                timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n            )\n            response.raise_for_status()\n            \n            self.session_id = response.headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\")\n            if not self.session_id:\n                raise ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")\n            \n            self.logger.info(f\"Bootstrapped session_id: {self.session_id}\")\n        finally:\n            session.close()\n    \n    def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\":\n        return self\n    \n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n        self.close()\n    \n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> Any:\n        \"\"\"Invoke the Agent Runtime with a JSON payload.\"\"\"\n        if not self.session_id:\n            raise ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")\n        \n        timeout_value = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n        \n        response = self.dp_client.invoke(\n            session_id=self.session_id,\n            payload=payload,\n            timeout=timeout_value,\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response.json()\n    \n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close the Agent Runtime client.\"\"\"\n        self.logger.info(\"Closing AgentRuntimeClient\")\n        if hasattr(self, \"dp_client\") and self.dp_client:\n            self.dp_client.close()\n```\n\n### 6. AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\nImplement in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`:\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ):\n        self.router_url = router_url\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.agent_name = agent_name\n        self.timeout = timeout\n        self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n        \n        base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n        self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n        \n        self.session = create_session(pool_connections=pool_connections, pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize)\n    \n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Bootstrap session_id via GET request.\"\"\"\n        response = self.session.get(\n            self.base_url,\n            timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        \n        session_id = response.headers.get(self.SESSION_HEADER)\n        if not session_id:\n            raise ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")\n        \n        return session_id\n    \n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> requests.Response:\n        \"\"\"Invoke the Agent Runtime with a JSON payload.\"\"\"\n        self.session.headers[self.SESSION_HEADER] = session_id\n        self.session.headers[\"Content-Type\"] = \"application/json\"\n        \n        timeout_value = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n        \n        response = self.session.post(\n            self.base_url,\n            json=payload,\n            timeout=(self.connect_timeout, timeout_value),\n        )\n        return response\n    \n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close the HTTP session.\"\"\"\n        self.session.close()\n```\n\n### 7. Utility Functions\n\nImplement in `agentcube/utils/http.py`:\n\n```python\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n    \"\"\"Create a requests Session with connection pooling.\"\"\"\n    session = requests.Session()\n    adapter = requests.adapters.HTTPAdapter(\n        pool_connections=pool_connections,\n        pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize,\n    )\n    session.mount(\"http://\", adapter)\n    session.mount(\"https://\", adapter)\n    return session\n```\n\nImplement in `agentcube/utils/utils.py`:\n\n```python\ndef read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Read token from file, returning empty string on FileNotFoundError.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        with open(file_path, \"r\") as f:\n            return f.read().strip()\n    except FileNotFoundError:\n        return \"\"\n```\n\nImplement in `agentcube/utils/log.py`:\n\n```python\ndef get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n    \"\"\"Get a logger with the specified name and level.\"\"\"\n    logger = logging.getLogger(name)\n    logger.setLevel(level)\n    \n    if not logger.handlers:\n        handler = logging.StreamHandler()\n        handler.setLevel(level)\n        formatter = logging.Formatter(\n            \"%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s\"\n        )\n        handler.setFormatter(formatter)\n        logger.addHandler(handler)\n    \n    return logger\n```\n\n### 8. Package Configuration\n\nCreate `pyproject.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\nname = \"agentcube-sdk\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\ndescription = \"AgentCube Python SDK for Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime\"\nreadme = \"README.md\"\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n\n[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\nwhere = [\".\"]\ninclude = [\"agentcube*\"]\nnamespaces = false\n```\n\n### 9. Module Exports\n\nImplement `agentcube/__init__.py`:\n\n```python\nfrom .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n```\n\nImplement `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`:\n\n```python\nfrom .control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\nfrom .code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\nfrom .agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n__all__ = [\n    \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n    \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n    \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n]\n```\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files to Create\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n| `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Client re-exports |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Control plane HTTP client |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Code Interpreter data plane client |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Agent Runtime data plane client |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | HTTP session factory |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Token reading utility |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Logger factory |\n| `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Module marker |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy |\n| `pyproject.toml` | Package configuration |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `requests` - HTTP client\n- `PyJWT>=2.0.0` - JWT handling (future extensibility)\n- `cryptography` - Cryptographic primitives (future extensibility)\n- Python >= 3.10\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\nThis is a new feature with no existing users. No backward compatibility concerns.\n\n### Testing Impact\n\nTest files should cover:\n\n- Context manager lifecycle and cleanup (`__enter__`, `__exit__`, `stop()`)\n- Session creation/deletion flows with control plane\n- Command execution with non-zero exit codes (raises `CommandExecutionError`)\n- File upload/download/write/list operations\n- Error handling (data plane init failure, missing URLs)\n- Environment variable fallback behavior (`ROUTER_URL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`)\n- Timeout handling with buffer (+2.0s for read timeout)\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Single Configuration Class\n\n**Approach:** Create a dedicated `Configuration` dataclass to hold all settings.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Centralized configuration management\n- Easier to validate at initialization\n\n**Cons:**\n- Adds unnecessary abstraction\n- Less flexible for per-client customization\n- More boilerplate\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Distributed configuration pattern is simpler and aligns with spec.\n\n### Alternative 2: Async HTTP Client\n\n**Approach:** Use `aiohttp` or `httpx` for async operations.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Better performance for concurrent operations\n- Modern async API\n\n**Cons:**\n- Increased complexity for users\n- Additional dependency burden\n- Not required for typical use cases\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Synchronous `requests` is sufficient and simpler.\n\n### Alternative 3: Automatic Session Reuse\n\n**Approach:** Automatically detect and reuse existing sessions by name/namespace.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Could reduce session creation overhead\n\n**Cons:**\n- Adds complexity\n- Potential for unintended session reuse\n- TTL-based cleanup becomes ambiguous\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Explicit `session_id` parameter provides clearer control.\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Create package structure (directories and `__init__.py` files)\n- [ ] Implement utility functions (http, utils, log)\n- [ ] Implement exception hierarchy\n- [ ] Implement `ControlPlaneClient`\n- [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n- [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n- [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterClient` with context manager\n- [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` with context manager\n- [ ] Create `pyproject.toml` with dependencies\n- [ ] Write unit tests for all clients\n- [ ] Write integration tests for session lifecycle\n- [ ] Create example usage scripts\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```python\n# tests/test_code_interpreter.py\n\nclass TestCodeInterpreterClient:\n    def test_context_manager_cleanup(self, mock_clients):\n        with CodeInterpreterClient(\n            router_url=\"http://test\",\n            workload_manager_url=\"http://wm\",\n        ) as client:\n            pass\n        \n        mock_clients.cp_client.delete_session.assert_called_once()\n        mock_clients.cp_client.close.assert_called_once()\n        mock_clients.dp_client.close.assert_called_once()\n    \n    def test_missing_router_url_raises(self):\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"router_url must be provided\"):\n            CodeInterpreterClient()\n    \n    def test_execute_command_nonzero_exit(self, mock_dp_client):\n        mock_dp_client.execute_command.side_effect = CommandExecutionError(\n            exit_code=1,\n            stderr=\"error message\",\n            command=[\"ls\", \"nonexistent\"],\n        )\n        \n        client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n            router_url=\"http://test\",\n            session_id=\"test-session\",\n        )\n        \n        with pytest.raises(CommandExecutionError) as exc_info:\n            client.execute_command(\"ls nonexistent\")\n        \n        assert exc_info.value.exit_code == 1\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```python\n# tests/test_integration.py\n\nclass TestIntegration:\n    @pytest.mark.skipif(not os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\"), reason=\"Requires ROUTER_URL\")\n    def test_full_lifecycle(self):\n        with CodeInterpreterClient(\n            name=\"test-interpreter\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            ttl=300,\n        ) as client:\n            # Execute command\n            result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n            assert \"hello\" in result\n            \n            # Write and execute Python code\n            code = \"print('test output')\"\n            result = client.run_code(\"python\", code)\n            assert \"test output\" in result\n            \n            # File operations\n            client.write_file(\"file content\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")\n            files = client.list_files(\"/tmp\")\n            assert any(\"test.txt\" in f for f in files)\n```\n\n## Future Considerations\n\n1. **Async support** - Add `AsyncCodeInterpreterClient` for async use cases\n2. **Streaming output** - Support streaming stdout/stderr for long-running commands\n3. **Session persistence** - Allow saving/restoring session state\n4. **Batch operations** - Execute multiple commands in a single request\n5. **Advanced file operations** - Support for directories, symlinks, permissions\n6. **Language extensions** - Support for more languages (JavaScript, Go, etc.)\n\n## References\n\n- Python SDK Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- Requests Documentation: https://requests.readthedocs.io/\n- Pydantic Documentation: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Criterion | Verification |\n|-----------|--------------|\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` creates session | Control plane `create_session` called when `session_id` not provided |\n| Context manager cleans up | `__exit__` calls `stop()`, deletes session, closes HTTP sessions |\n| Command execution works | `execute_command` returns stdout on success |\n| Non-zero exit raises | `CommandExecutionError` raised with exit_code, stderr |\n| File operations work | `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files` functional |\n| Router URL validation | `ValueError` raised if `router_url` and `ROUTER_URL` both missing |\n| Session header correct | `x-agentcube-session-id` used (lowercase) |\n| Timeout buffer applied | Read timeout = request timeout + 2.0s |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` bootstraps | GET invocation endpoint to obtain `session_id` |\n| Package installs | `pip install .` succeeds, imports work |\n\n---\n\n**Document Version:** 1.0  \n**Last Updated:** 2026-04-11  \n**Author:** AgentCube Team  \n**Contact:** agentcube@volcano.sh  \n**AR:** AR-027  \n**Module:** `sdk-python`\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_027.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_027.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_027.md","time":{"start":1775874972991,"end":1775874973002}}}}
